Q136. LeetCode : Single Number ?


Q137. LeetCode: Single Number || ?
ðŸ”¹ Step-by-Step Implementation :
Step 1: Take Input
int arr [] = {2,2,3,2}
Step 2: Initialize Result Variable 
int res = 0;
         - res will store the final unique number
         - Initially all bits are 0
Step 3: Traverse Bit Positions (0 â†’ 31)
for (int i = 0; i < 32; i++)
         - Java int = 32 bits
         - We check each bit position independently
Step 4: Count Set Bits at Position i
int bitCount = 0;

for (int num : arr) {
    if ((num & (1 << i)) != 0) {
        bitCount++;
    }
}
         - 1 << i â†’ mask for i-th bit
         - num & mask != 0 â†’ i-th bit is set
         - Count how many numbers have that bit set
Step 5: Remove Triplet Effect
if (bitCount % 3 != 0) {
    res = res | (1 << i);
}
         - Numbers repeating 3 times cancel out
         - Remaining bit belongs to the single number
Step 6: Print Result
System.out.println(res);



